{
  "AC": "tag command prints {embedder:{tag:score}} top-k per embedder, recomputed each run; candidate domain = 1/2/3-grams mined from corpus; per-embedder cosine top-k; tags not persisted durably; refresh fn shared by search and tag; tests cover mining, per-embedder top-k, non-persistence",
  "ActualSummary": "Shipped `tag`: zero-shot semantic tagging, printing {embedder: {tag: score}},\ntop-k per embedder (-k, default 3), recomputed each run, never persisted.\nCandidate domain = 1/2/3 n-phrases mined corpus-wide, so a todo can get a\nphrase it never uses. Added n-phrase chunking (one vector per window) to the\nembed write path. Extracted shared _refresh_embeddings/_load_corpus/\n_resolve_embedders and made them read corpus + vectors through the store\n(inline vectors, backend-agnostic), so search AND tag now work on the\nJSON-directory backend, not just sqlite. Wired doctor to refresh corpus\nembeddings (backfill-empty, trust-existing, tolerant of an unavailable\nbackend). 150 tests pass, including JSON-backend tag and doctor-refresh\ncoverage. Kept it simple per the plan: no hubness correction, no linguistic\npruning (noted as future work).",
  "BaseSha": "8337e085e1bc0b27f818739cfc500e3185152f7e",
