    "raw": "Goal: add a top-level `tags` field to todos, shape {embedder: {tag: score}},\ntop-k (~3) tags per embedder. Zero-shot semantic tagging over a candidate\ndomain of 1/2/3-grams (\"n-phrases\") mined from the whole corpus (Summary+Body\nraw of every todo).\n\nDesign (from /tmp/foo):\n- Candidate domain: 1,2,3-grams (n-phrases; split on phrase separators:\n  sentences, headings, ascii art) across the whole corpus. Pruning is a TODO\n  and may not be needed. Linguistic pruning dropped for now (must stay\n  programmatic, no agent intervention).\n- For each (todo doc-embedding x candidate tag) compute cosine; keep k highest\n  per embedder. Scores from different embedders are NOT comparable, so each\n  embedder gets its own top-k set.\n- Tags are NOT persisted durably: recomputed each run (along with the embedding\n  refresh). The field is a computed/merged view produced at tag/read time, not\n  written back to the store.\n- Entry points: a new `tag` command, and wired into `doctor`. Default embedder\n  set = all available (as search does); availability comes from the entry point.\n\nReuse / prerequisites:\n- Shared refresh function: extract the lazy vector backfill currently inside\n  search (todo.py ~1132-1143) into an internal \"refresh embeddings for all\n  todos\" used by BOTH search and tag. Trust existing vectors; recompute only\n  empties. Field edits already zero their vectors (_strip_field_vectors on\n  changed raw).\n- n-phrase chunking: today each field is ONE chunk (todo.py:476, \"until\n  chunking lands the whole field is one chunk\"). foo \"Managing embeddings\"\n  wants 1,2,3 n-phrase chunking for Summary/Body. SCOPE QUESTION: do chunking\n  in this todo, or ship tags against whole-field vectors first and treat\n  chunking as a sibling todo.\n- Stored chunks are bare vectors with no source text, so candidate tag\n  embeddings must be computed fresh per embedder (cannot reverse-map a chunk\n  vector back to its tag string).\n\nTouch points: todo.py (embed helpers ~355-520; search/refresh ~1085-1170;\ndoctor cmd; new `tag` cmd + argparse), todo_embed.py (embedders/cosine),\ntodo_store.py + todo_db.py (read-only: corpus text + stored vectors). Tests:\ntest_todo.py, test_todo_embed*.py.\n\nOpen decisions (confirm before init + implementation):\n1. Scope: include n-phrase chunking here, or tags-only against current\n   whole-field vectors (chunking as a sibling todo)?\n2. Isolation: repo jovlinger/utils is on master with uncommitted WIP (M todo.py,\n   SKILL.md, ...). Need a worktree/branch strategy that does not entangle it."
  },
